The paper deals with the problem of string indexing, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The packed variant of the problem involves storing multiple characters in a single word, which is a technique commonly used in algorithms for efficient memory access and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves analyzing the time and space complexity of the algorithm, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of logarithmic terms in the query time suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper involves experimental results and comparisons with previous algorithms, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG).
